# Commitly AI Conventions

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router, React 19)
- **Database**: Supabase (PostgreSQL)
- **Auth**: NextAuth v5 (Credentials, Google, GitHub)
- **AI**: Vercel AI SDK + OpenAI (gpt-4o-mini)
- **Background Jobs**: Inngest
- **Payments**: Stripe
- **Email**: Resend
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4, Lucide icons

## Naming
- **Page files**: `page.tsx` in route folder (`src/app/dashboard/page.tsx`)
- **API routes**: `route.ts` with HTTP exports (`src/app/api/stripe/webhook/route.ts`)
- **Server actions**: `actions.ts` in feature folder (`src/app/dashboard/actions.ts`)
- **Components**: PascalCase (`RepoPicker.tsx`, `BrandVoiceForm.tsx`)
- **Lib modules**: camelCase (`release-drafts.ts`, `users.ts`)
- **DB tables**: snake_case plural (`users`, `release_drafts`)
- **Env vars**: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (`STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`)

## Backend Patterns
- **DB access**: Always use `supabaseAdmin` from `lib/supabase/server.ts`
- **Auth check**: Call `auth()` + check `session?.user` at start of protected routes
- **User lookup**: Use `getOrCreateUser(authId, email)` to get DB user from session
- **Long tasks**: Send to Inngest via `inngest.send()`, never block API routes
- **Subscription checks**: Use `canCreateDraft()` / `canConnectRepo()` from `lib/subscription.ts`

## Frontend Patterns
- **Protected pages**: Async server components with `auth()` check, `redirect("/signin")` if null
- **Forms**: Client components with server actions, use `revalidatePath()` after mutations
- **Icons**: Import from `lucide-react`, use `strokeWidth={1.5}` in sidebar/chrome
- **UI/UX spec**: `.cursor/plans/Ui-design-spec.md` is the visual north star (colors, tokens, layout)
- **Theme**: `next-themes` ThemeProvider in root layout; class-based dark mode
- **App shell**: `src/components/dashboard/dashboard-shell.tsx` — shared sidebar + top bar for all `/dashboard/*` routes
- **Server actions for client components**: Place in co-located `actions.ts` with `"use server"` — never inline in client component files
- **Accent/brand color**: Use `text-brand` / `bg-brand` for violet accents; `bg-primary` / `text-primary-foreground` for black CTAs
- **Border radius**: Prefer `rounded-xl` / `rounded-2xl` for cards, inputs, buttons per spec

## Package Manager
Use `npm` (see `package-lock.json`).

